    {
      "title": "What are Ordinal Numbers?",
      "titleArabic": "مَا هِيَ الأَعْدَادُ التَّرْتِيبِيَّةُ؟",
      "content": [
        "الأَعْدَاد التَّرْتِيبِيَّة (ordinal numbers) indicate position in a sequence: first, second, third, etc. They answer 'which number in order?' rather than 'how many?'",
        "Unlike cardinal numbers (أَعْدَاد أَصْلِيَّة) which count quantity, ordinals show rank or sequence. They behave grammatically like adjectives (صِفَات) and follow the noun they describe."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Indicate position in sequence",
        "الأَوَّل، الثَّانِي، الثَّالِث...",
        "Function as adjectives",
        "Follow the described noun"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "الْكِتَابُ الأَوَّلُ", "english": "The first book" },
        { "arabic": "الطَّالِبَةُ الثَّانِيَةُ", "english": "The second (female) student" },
        { "arabic": "الْفَصْلُ الثَّالِثُ", "english": "The third chapter" },
        { "arabic": "السَّنَةُ الرَّابِعَةُ", "english": "The fourth year" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Ordinals 1-10",
      "titleArabic": "التَّرْتِيبِيَّةُ مِنْ 1-10",
      "content": [
        "The ordinals 1-10 follow the pattern فَاعِل (for 1-10 masculine): أَوَّل، ثَانٍ، ثَالِث، رَابِع، خَامِس، سَادِس، سَابِع، ثَامِن، تَاسِع، عَاشِر.",
        "For feminine, add ة: أُولَى، ثَانِيَة، ثَالِثَة، رَابِعَة، خَامِسَة، سَادِسَة، سَابِعَة، ثَامِنَة، تَاسِعَة، عَاشِرَة. Note: أَوَّل becomes أُولَى (not *أَوَّلَة)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Masculine: فَاعِل pattern",
        "Feminine: add ة (except أُولَى)",
        "ثَانٍ: deficient noun (الاسم المنقوص)",
        "Agree with described noun in gender"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "أَوَّل / أُولَى", "english": "First (m/f)" },
        { "arabic": "ثَانٍ / ثَانِيَة", "english": "Second (m/f)" },
        { "arabic": "ثَالِث / ثَالِثَة", "english": "Third (m/f)" },
        { "arabic": "رَابِع، خَامِس، سَادِس، سَابِع، ثَامِن، تَاسِع، عَاشِر", "english": "4th, 5th, 6th, 7th, 8th, 9th, 10th (masc)" }
      ]
    },
