      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Both parts agree in gender",
        "Masculine: الثَّالِثَ عَشَرَ",
        "Feminine: الثَّالِثَةَ عَشْرَةَ",
        "مَبْنِيّ على فتح الجزأين"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "الْكِتَابُ الْحَادِي عَشَرَ", "english": "The eleventh book" },
        { "arabic": "الصَّفْحَةُ الثَّانِيَةَ عَشْرَةَ", "english": "The twelfth page" },
        { "arabic": "الْقَرْنُ الْخَامِسَ عَشَرَ", "english": "The fifteenth century" },
        { "arabic": "السَّنَةُ التَّاسِعَةَ عَشْرَةَ", "english": "The nineteenth year" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Ordinals 20 and Above",
      "titleArabic": "التَّرْتِيبِيَّةُ مِنْ 20 فَأَكْثَر",
      "content": [
        "For tens (20, 30, etc.), the cardinal form is used as ordinal: الْعِشْرُونَ، الثَّلَاثُونَ، الأَرْبَعُونَ... These don't have separate ordinal forms.",
        "For compounds (21, 22, etc.), the units are ordinal and the tens are cardinal: الْحَادِي وَالْعِشْرُونَ، الثَّانِي وَالْعِشْرُونَ. The unit's ordinal agrees in gender with the noun."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
